Basic idea:
cKDTrees can be pickled and loading pickles is much faster than rebuilding trees
every time. Simply build the trees once when the data is first loaded and then
store them for later use.

Plans for the branch:
- A cache location is mandatory and is used to store pickled KDTrees
- PatchCatalog.data is no longer a DataFrame but creates them on request
- Attribtues directly link to PatchCatalog.tree
- The SphericalKDTree has an additional attribute for redshifts and RA and DEC
- The SphericalKDTree has a __getstate__ and __setstate__ method to not store
  the RA and DEC data twice
- Create a BasePatchCatalog object with some common methods between backends,
  which just serves as a wrapper around the underlying data structures
